Let's concentrate
on what we do have--

474
00:28:00,946 --> 00:28:03,015
each other.

475
00:28:03,015 --> 00:28:04,283
Yeah.
Right.

476
00:28:04,283 --> 00:28:06,285
You got it, Coach.
You got it.

477
00:28:06,285 --> 00:28:08,353
All for one.
That's right.

478
00:28:08,353 --> 00:28:10,289
All right, guys, let's go!
All for one!

479
00:28:10,289 --> 00:28:12,758
Let's go play.
Let's go have fun!
Come on!

480
00:28:15,527 --> 00:28:17,529
[chattering]

481
00:28:17,529 --> 00:28:19,231
Come on, come on.

482
00:28:19,231 --> 00:28:21,366
Go back, back.

483
00:28:21,366 --> 00:28:23,368
Doc.

484
00:28:23,368 --> 00:28:25,237
What's up?

485
00:28:25,237 --> 00:28:27,506
Feel like starting tomorrow?

486
00:28:27,506 --> 00:28:30,042
Yeah. Where? Columbus?

487
00:28:30,042 --> 00:28:32,077
I need somebody
to start tomorrow
against Seattle.

488
00:28:32,077 --> 00:28:34,112
It's yours if you want it.

489
00:28:37,249 --> 00:28:39,217
Yeah.

490
00:28:43,522 --> 00:28:45,123
[chuckles]

491
00:28:58,236 --> 00:29:00,238
[sighs]

492
00:29:07,045 --> 00:29:08,747
[grunts]

493
00:29:14,386 --> 00:29:16,288
[grunts]

494
00:29:20,559 --> 00:29:23,195
Let's hope
he can pitch like that
with his clothes on.

495
00:29:23,195 --> 00:29:25,764
Shh, shh, shh,
shh, shh! Shh!

496
00:29:38,844 --> 00:29:41,046
I don't know
what to do, Joe.

497
00:29:42,581 --> 00:29:45,317
I mean, if this is gonna be
his last hours,

498
00:29:45,317 --> 00:29:48,053
I think I should
be there, right?

499
00:29:48,053 --> 00:29:50,055
Have you talked to him?

500
00:29:50,055 --> 00:29:52,324
I didn't know
what to tell him.

501
00:29:52,324 --> 00:29:56,194
I just kind of wanted
to make up my mind first.

502
00:29:57,329 --> 00:29:59,798
I mean, he always said
that if...

503
00:30:00,866 --> 00:30:02,868
[stifled crying]

504
00:30:09,474 --> 00:30:13,211
He said he never wanted me
to lose my turn.

505
00:30:13,211 --> 00:30:15,847
So...

506
00:30:23,088 --> 00:30:24,823
[paper rustling]

507
00:30:25,624 --> 00:30:28,260
[mutters]

508
00:30:28,260 --> 00:30:31,363
[phone buttons clicking]

509
00:30:36,201 --> 00:30:38,203
Dan Gooden.

510
00:30:42,274 --> 00:30:45,110
Dad, it's Dwight.
How you doing?

511
00:30:46,511 --> 00:30:50,649
'Cause you know
I'll be on the next flight.

512
00:30:50,649 --> 00:30:53,852
Because I'd like
to be there with you,
that's why.

513
00:30:57,355 --> 00:30:59,124
Right.

514
00:31:02,194 --> 00:31:03,862
Right.

515
00:31:05,931 --> 00:31:07,632
Okay. Right.

516
00:31:07,632 --> 00:31:09,568
First thing in the morning.

517
00:31:11,536 --> 00:31:13,538
I love you.

518
00:31:20,145 --> 00:31:23,515
He says, uh, the operation
is first thing in the morning.

519
00:31:23,515 --> 00:31:25,550
They're gonna give him
something to sleep,

520
00:31:25,550 --> 00:31:27,686
and he'll be knocked out
