00:39:08,446 --> 00:39:11,015
No, it's a problem,
because if you don't
keep reminding yourself of that,

679
00:39:11,015 --> 00:39:13,918
you're gonna go back
to trying to pull everything.
Joe. Joe, Ali's on the phone.

680
00:39:13,918 --> 00:39:16,087
Listen, I think I'm gonna
sit Paulie for the second game.

681
00:39:16,087 --> 00:39:18,923
Yeah. You need to think
about Girardi too.
He took some bad foul tips.

682
00:39:18,923 --> 00:39:20,758
Yeah.

683
00:39:20,758 --> 00:39:22,193
Hi, sweetie.
What's up?

684
00:39:22,193 --> 00:39:24,862
Joe, are you sitting down?

685
00:39:26,764 --> 00:39:28,032
Frank?

686
00:39:31,669 --> 00:39:33,671
It's Rocco, Joe.

687
00:39:35,039 --> 00:39:37,875
He, uh--
He had a heart attack.

688
00:39:37,875 --> 00:39:42,046
Christ.
What hospital is he in?

689
00:39:44,816 --> 00:39:46,884
No hospital, Joe.

690
00:39:53,124 --> 00:39:55,126
[phone clicks in cradle]

691
00:40:21,886 --> 00:40:24,689
Roc...

692
00:40:24,689 --> 00:40:26,924
we won the second game 9 to 3

693
00:40:26,924 --> 00:40:28,693
behind Mendoza.

694
00:40:28,693 --> 00:40:30,695
It was a blowout.

695
00:40:31,729 --> 00:40:34,165
We're in first place.

696
00:40:34,165 --> 00:40:37,168
This is the lineup card.
I wanted you to have it.

697
00:40:43,841 --> 00:40:47,211
And all the guys
signed this.

698
00:40:51,182 --> 00:40:53,451
I'm gonna win it this time.

699
00:40:59,023 --> 00:41:01,526
Christ, I wanted you
to be there.

700
00:41:09,300 --> 00:41:11,002
[knock on door]

701
00:41:11,002 --> 00:41:12,770
Come in.
[door opens]

702
00:41:12,770 --> 00:41:15,807
You wanted me, boss?
Where's Darryl Strawberry?

703
00:41:15,807 --> 00:41:17,809
We didn't sign him.

704
00:41:17,809 --> 00:41:20,845
You mean he's available?
I mean, he's out of baseball.

705
00:41:20,845 --> 00:41:22,880
Nobody wanted him.
Find him.

706
00:41:22,880 --> 00:41:24,882
What the hell am I
gonna do with him?

707
00:41:24,882 --> 00:41:26,951
Who am I gonna sit down?

708
00:41:26,951 --> 00:41:28,319
DH, I guess.

709
00:41:28,319 --> 00:41:30,221
You could put him
in the outfield.

710
00:41:30,221 --> 00:41:32,223
Hell, I don't know.

711
00:41:32,223 --> 00:41:35,126
I got no room
for him, Zim.

712
00:41:35,126 --> 00:41:38,329
Well, he was a hell
of a hitter.

713
00:41:38,329 --> 00:41:40,965
We could sure use
some good offense now.

714
00:41:40,965 --> 00:41:43,868
Can he still hit?
Do you know?
I don't know.

715
00:41:43,868 --> 00:41:46,838
[chattering]

716
00:41:59,083 --> 00:42:01,119
Hey, Darryl.

717
00:42:01,119 --> 00:42:04,122
What's up, brother?
[laughs]

718
00:42:06,057 --> 00:42:07,825
About time, cuz.

719
00:42:07,825 --> 00:42:10,094
It's good to be here, Doc.

720
00:42:10,094 --> 00:42:11,796
Hey, welcome to the zoo, man.

721
00:42:11,796 --> 00:42:13,331
Welcome to the dark side, man.

722
00:42:13,331 --> 00:42:14,966
You gonna do some banging
for us, huh?

723
00:42:14,966 --> 00:42:17,802
Maybe later.

724
00:42:17,802 --> 00:42:20,171
Right now I gotta
go see the man.

725
00:42:21,873 --> 00:42:24,108
See you later, man.
See you later.

726
00:42:24,108 --> 00:42:27,578
[chattering]

727
00:42:35,219 --> 00:42:38,089
Hello, Darryl.

728
00:42:38,089 --> 00:42:40,291
Hey, chief.
I just wanted to say

729
00:42:40,291 --> 00:42:43,227
that I'm here to do
whatever you need me to do.

730
00:42:43,227 --> 00:42:44,996
I appreciate that.

731
00:42:44,996 --> 00:42:46,998
I don't know what
you've heard about me, but--

732
00:42:46,998 --> 00:42:49,000
I've heard it all.

733
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:50,368
But I just wanted to say that--

734
00:42:50,368 --> 00:42:53,371
Darryl, as far
as I am concerned,

735
00:42:53,371 --> 00:42:55,573
history starts today.

736
00:42:58,976 --> 00:43:00,912
[shaking hands]
Thanks, skipper.

737
00:43:00,912 --> 00:43:03,381
<i>[TV announcer]</i>
<i>The pitch.</i>
<i>Strawberry launches one!</i>

738
00:43:03,381 --> 00:43:05,983
[crowd cheering]
<i>It is high, it is far!</i>

739
00:43:05,983 --> 00:43:07,385
<i>It is gone!</i>

740
00:43:07,385 --> 00:43:10,988
<i>A long home run</i>
<i>for Darryl Strawberry!</i>

741
00:43:10,988 --> 00:43:13,391
<i> [radio show host]</i>
<i> You're on the air.</i>
<i> What do you wanna talk about?</i>

742
00:43:13,391 --> 00:43:15,293
<i>[radio show caller]</i>
<i>I'll tell you what it is.</i>

743
00:43:15,293 --> 00:43:17,995
<i>Joe Torre's got these guys</i>
<i>playing together like a team.</i>

744
00:43:17,995 --> 00:43:21,265
<i>No stars, just a team.</i>
<i> You're up.</i>

745
00:43:21,265 --> 00:43:24,302
<i>[caller #2] I'll tell you</i>
<i>what the difference is.</i>
<i>It's Joe Torre.</i>

746
00:43:24,302 --> 00:43:27,872
<i>They're playing for this guy</i>
<i>the way he used to play.</i>

747
00:43:27,872 --> 00:43:30,274
[cheering fading out]

748
00:44:02,073 --> 00:44:04,141
Rae, it's Joe.
What's happening?

749
00:44:04,141 --> 00:44:07,211
I'm-- I'm worried sick, Joey.

750
00:44:07,211 --> 00:44:09,213
<i> I thought he was going</i>
<i> to the doctor.</i>

751
00:44:09,213 --> 00:44:11,115
He's gone to everybody--

752
00:44:11,115 --> 00:44:13,084
this doctor, that doctor--

753
00:44:13,084 --> 00:44:15,386
and it's getting
worse and worse.

754
00:44:17,922 --> 00:44:21,325
I think-- I think
he just gave up, Joey.

755
00:44:23,327 --> 00:44:27,198
Rocco dying seemed to just
take everything out of him.

756
00:44:27,198 --> 00:44:30,034
You just listen to me, Rae.
We lost Rocco.

757
00:44:30,034 --> 00:44:32,303
We are not gonna lose Frankie.
Do you hear me?

758
00:44:34,071 --> 00:44:36,073
What's she doing?
Is she talking to Joey?

759
00:44:36,073 --> 00:44:39,043
Mm.
What's she bothering him for?

760
00:44:39,043 --> 00:44:41,946
Rae, put him on.

761
00:44:45,082 --> 00:44:47,318
Tsk.

762
00:44:47,318 --> 00:44:51,088
[sighs]
Hey, Joey.

763
00:44:51,088 --> 00:44:53,758
What the hell
do you want from me?
I'm getting old, that's all.

764
00:44:53,758 --> 00:44:56,427
<i> There's nothing</i>
<i> anybody can do about it.</i>

765
00:44:56,427 --> 00:44:58,963
You are so stupid,
you know that, Frankie?

766
00:44:58,963 --> 00:45:02,266
Hey, Joey, come on now.

767
00:45:02,266 --> 00:45:05,169
I'm your older brother,
remember?
A little respect.

768
00:45:05,169 --> 00:45:07,371
I show you respect.

769
00:45:07,371 --> 00:45:11,342
But I'm not gonna
take it easy on you.
Did you ever take it easy on me?

770
00:45:11,342 --> 00:45:14,345
<i>When I was just</i>
<i>out of high school and no team</i>
<i>would take a look at me,</i>

771
00:45:14,345 --> 00:45:16,347
<i> did you take it easy on me?</i>

772
00:45:16,347 --> 00:45:17,348
Joey.

773
00:45:17,348 --> 00:45:20,151
Let me talk!

774
00:45:23,788 --> 00:45:26,257
You made me take off the weight,
you made me into a catcher,

775
00:45:26,257 --> 00:45:28,125
and it worked out good,
didn't it?

776
00:45:28,125 --> 00:45:30,795
Yeah. What the hell
does that got to do with it?

777
00:45:30,795 --> 00:45:32,430
It's got everything
to do with it.

778
00:45:32,430 --> 00:45:34,999
You didn't let me quit,
and I'm not gonna let you quit.

779
00:45:34,999 --> 00:45:37,234
No way. If the doctors
down there can't help you,

780
00:45:37,234 --> 00:45:39,003
then you'll come up to New York.

781
00:45:39,003 --> 00:45:40,438
We have the best doctors
in New York.

782
00:45:40,438 --> 00:45:44,075
But I got nothing in the tank.
What the hell is the point?

783
00:45:44,075 --> 00:45:47,044
The point is, I have lost
one brother this year,

784
00:45:47,044 --> 00:45:49,246
and I am not gonna
lose another one.

785
00:45:50,314 --> 00:45:52,049
[sighs]

786
00:45:53,317 --> 00:45:55,319
[sirens wailing]

787
00:45:55,319 --> 00:45:57,521
<i>[radio show host]</i>
<i>Tony from Tenafly, you're up.</i>

788
00:45:57,521 --> 00:46:00,324
<i> [Tony]</i>
<i> These guys are trying</i>
<i> to drive me crazy.</i>

789
00:46:00,324 --> 00:46:03,327
<i> They sweep the Orioles,</i>
<i> they got a 12-and-a-half</i>
<i> game lead.</i>

790
00:46:03,327 --> 00:46:05,896
<i> It's all over, right?</i>
<i> Wrong.</i>

791
00:46:05,896 --> 00:46:09,333
<i> They lost five games</i>
<i> this week.</i>
<i> Here come the Orioles.</i>

792
00:46:09,333 --> 00:46:11,569
<i> Unless these clowns</i>
<i> get their act together--</i>

793
00:46:11,569 --> 00:46:15,106
<i>Sal from the Bronx,</i>
<i>you're on the air.</i>
<i>What's on your mind?</i>

794
00:46:15,106 --> 00:46:17,408
<i> [Sal]</i>
<i> Hey, come on. What's</i>
<i> everybody panicking about?</i>

795
00:46:17,408 --> 00:46:19,844
<i> They're still in first place,</i>
<i> ain't they?</i>

796
00:47:22,306 --> 00:47:24,508
Mm. Hi.

797
00:47:25,643 --> 00:47:27,311
Hi.

798
00:47:27,311 --> 00:47:29,313
I was trying
not to wake you up.

799
00:47:30,514 --> 00:47:32,516
I've been waiting for you.

800
00:47:32,516 --> 00:47:34,118
Yeah?

801
00:47:34,118 --> 00:47:35,619
Come.

802
00:47:46,163 --> 00:47:47,398
[sighs]

803
00:47:49,133 --> 00:47:50,434
Tired?

804
00:47:53,404 --> 00:47:55,206
Been a long time.

805
00:47:55,206 --> 00:47:57,141
I've been on the road
too long.

806
00:47:57,141 --> 00:47:58,342
Mmm.

807
00:48:09,620 --> 00:48:11,555
Skip, it's just a strain.

808
00:48:11,555 --> 00:48:16,160
He should be able to throw again
in ten days, maybe two weeks.

809
00:48:16,160 --> 00:48:19,430
If we had to pick one guy
we couldn't afford to lose...
Yeah. No kidding.

810
00:48:19,430 --> 00:48:22,199
Well, it's gonna
screw up the bullpen
for a couple of weeks,

811
00:48:22,199 --> 00:48:24,468
but I think we can handle it.

812
00:48:24,468 --> 00:48:26,670
They damn well
better handle it.

813
00:48:27,705 --> 00:48:29,440
Okay.

814
00:48:31,342 --> 00:48:33,911
[chattering]

815
00:48:38,182 --> 00:48:39,316
<i> [bat smacks ball]</i>

816
00:48:39,316 --> 00:48:42,286
Oh, no, no, no, no, no!
[exclaims]

817
00:48:42,286 --> 00:48:43,721
<i>[crowd cheering] </i>
What?

818
00:48:43,721 --> 00:48:46,223
The Orioles
just tied it up.

819
00:48:46,223 --> 00:48:47,758
Are we playing 'em?

820
00:48:47,758 --> 00:48:50,294
No.
Then what do you care
what they do?

821
00:48:50,294 --> 00:48:52,763
We were 12 games up.
Now it's only seven.

822
00:48:52,763 --> 00:48:56,300
We are seven games up,
they are seven games down,

823
00:48:56,300 --> 00:48:58,302
and we're the ones
who are worrying?

824
00:48:58,302 --> 00:49:00,404
They must be about ready
to kill themselves.

825
00:49:00,404 --> 00:49:03,707
[chuckling]

826
00:49:07,511 --> 00:49:10,281
Hey, how you doing?

827
00:49:10,281 --> 00:49:13,617
<i> [Woman on P.A., indistinct]</i>

828
00:49:16,420 --> 00:49:19,457
Oh, there's Rae.
Where's Frankie?

829
00:49:19,457 --> 00:49:21,458
[no audible dialogue]

830
00:49:29,400 --> 00:49:31,468
Hey, Joey.

831
00:49:31,468 --> 00:49:33,437
How are ya?
Good to see ya.

832
00:49:33,437 --> 00:49:35,606
Hey, Joey.
[laughs]

833
00:49:35,606 --> 00:49:37,608
How are ya, kid?
Hi.

834
00:49:37,608 --> 00:49:40,544
How you doing?
How am I doing?

835
00:49:41,545 --> 00:49:44,381
Eh, I don't know, Joey.

836
00:49:44,381 --> 00:49:45,783
I don't know.
It's all right.

837
00:49:45,783 --> 00:49:48,385
We're gonna get you fixed up,
okay? Okay.
Yeah?

838
00:49:48,385 --> 00:49:49,787
Yeah. Come here.
Give him to me.

839
00:49:49,787 --> 00:49:52,256
Hey, lookit...

840
00:49:56,393 --> 00:49:57,795
We have him stabilized.

841
00:49:57,795 --> 00:49:59,797
I wish I could tell you more,
but we don't know yet.

842
00:49:59,797 --> 00:50:01,565
I'll be running
some tests tomorrow.

843
00:50:01,565 --> 00:50:04,068
I'll have
some answers for you
in a couple of days.

844
00:50:04,068 --> 00:50:06,070
Thank you.

845
00:50:07,638 --> 00:50:10,274
<i> ♪♪ [rock] </i>
[chattering]

846
00:50:13,677 --> 00:50:15,846
Hey!
All right!

847
00:50:15,846 --> 00:50:17,781
Hey, Doc.

848
00:50:19,450 --> 00:50:22,553
Looking good, man.
[mutters]

849
00:50:22,553 --> 00:50:25,289
Hey, Coney, you here
to save our asses, man?

850
00:50:25,289 --> 00:50:27,791
[laughter]
Coney, Coney, Coney, Coney.

851
00:50:27,791 --> 00:50:30,427
I miss you so much.
[laughter]

852
00:50:33,597 --> 00:50:35,599
All right!

853
00:50:35,599 --> 00:50:37,635
We got ourselves a Coney.
He's back.

854
00:50:37,635 --> 00:50:39,637
He's back, and he's bad.
He's badder than ever.

855
00:50:39,637 --> 00:50:41,872
<i> ♪♪ [continues]</i>

856
00:50:41,872 --> 00:50:44,108
What do you think of that?

857
00:51:00,524 --> 00:51:02,760
Don't push it, Coney.
[grunts]

858
00:51:02,760 --> 00:51:05,195
It's coming back, Joe.

859
00:51:05,195 --> 00:51:08,198
I'll be back
before the season's over.

860
00:51:08,198 --> 00:51:10,834
Five more minutes,
then shut it down.

861
00:51:14,672 --> 00:51:16,907
What do you think?

862
00:51:16,907 --> 00:51:18,909
Kid's got guts.

863
00:51:18,909 --> 00:51:21,745
Is that a yes?

864
00:51:21,745 --> 00:51:24,748
I don't know, Joe.

865
00:51:24,748 --> 00:51:26,750
I don't know.

866
00:51:26,750 --> 00:51:29,753
<i>[TV announcer]</i>
<i>Left-hander Lloyd</i>
<i>on the mound.</i>

867
00:51:29,753 --> 00:51:33,591
<i>Stares in for the sign.</i>
<i>Working out of the stretch,</i>

868
00:51:33,591 --> 00:51:35,559
<i>he sets up the letters</i>
<i>and delivers. </i>
[bat smacks ball]

869
00:51:35,559 --> 00:51:37,461
[crowd cheering]
<i>Driven deep</i>
<i>to right center field.</i>

870
00:51:37,461 --> 00:51:39,630
<i>O'Neill giving chase.</i>
<i>And he pulls up.</i>

871
00:51:39,630 --> 00:51:41,865
[crowd groaning]
<i>That's a ball that O'Neill</i>
<i>really should catch.</i>

872
00:51:41,865 --> 00:51:43,867
[crowd jeering]

873
00:51:51,609 --> 00:51:52,643
[grunts]

874
00:51:58,415 --> 00:52:00,417
Am I out?
You're hurting, Paulie.

875
00:52:00,417 --> 00:52:03,854
I'm gonna put Ruben in.
Take the rest of the day off.

876
00:52:03,854 --> 00:52:06,490
Paulie...

877
00:52:06,490 --> 00:52:08,525
we got
a long way to go.

878
00:52:11,395 --> 00:52:13,497
Your brother
needs a new heart.

879
00:52:17,401 --> 00:52:18,802
A new heart?

880
00:52:18,802 --> 00:52:22,406
Actually, Joe,
the surgery's the simplest part.

881
00:52:22,406 --> 00:52:25,542
The hard part
is finding a donor.
We have to wait.

882
00:52:25,542 --> 00:52:27,678
Well, how long
does that take?

883
00:52:27,678 --> 00:52:29,680
There's no way to tell.
If we're lucky,

884
00:52:29,680 --> 00:52:32,750
we could find one tomorrow,
but it really could take months.

885
00:52:32,750 --> 00:52:36,587
What?
Two, three, five?

886
00:52:36,587 --> 00:52:38,589
I'll be honest
with you, Sister.

887
00:52:38,589 --> 00:52:40,858
I don't think your brother
has that much time.

888
00:52:55,606 --> 00:52:57,674
You wanna talk about it?

889
00:52:59,643 --> 00:53:02,179
Nothing to talk about,
really.

890
00:53:03,881 --> 00:53:07,317
Not talking about it
won't make it go away, Joe.

891
00:53:09,853 --> 00:53:11,588
No.

892
00:53:17,561 --> 00:53:20,664
See, I was this little kid
from Brooklyn.

893
00:53:20,664 --> 00:53:23,600
But it's like
I grew up too late.

894
00:53:23,600 --> 00:53:27,004
My brothers and sisters
were already grown up.

895
00:53:27,004 --> 00:53:30,541
And the house was a madhouse.

896
00:53:30,541 --> 00:53:33,277
My father was always
hitting my mom.
You know that.

897
00:53:35,045 --> 00:53:37,681
Scared the shit out of me.

898
00:53:39,483 --> 00:53:42,753
You know the story
about how Frank threw him out?

899
00:53:42,753 --> 00:53:44,922
He had a lot of guts.

900
00:53:47,691 --> 00:53:49,993
He was everything
I wanted to be.

901
00:53:49,993 --> 00:53:52,496
He was my hero.

902
00:53:52,496 --> 00:53:55,032
He was a major leaguer.

903
00:53:55,032 --> 00:53:57,534
He was in the World Series.

904
00:53:59,970 --> 00:54:02,072
You will be too.
Yeah.

905
00:54:02,072 --> 00:54:04,708
But here's the thing, Ali.

906
00:54:07,745 --> 00:54:10,280
I get this shot
out of nowhere...

907
00:54:12,516 --> 00:54:15,853
and just as I'm
about to get there,

908
00:54:15,853 --> 00:54:17,855
my brothers...

909
00:54:22,793 --> 00:54:25,929
Rocco won't be there,

910
00:54:25,929 --> 00:54:28,832
and probably Frank
won't be there.

911
00:54:31,034 --> 00:54:35,005
It's like I wake up
out of one nightmare,

912
00:54:35,005 --> 00:54:37,641
and I'm in the middle
of another one.

913
00:54:40,744 --> 00:54:42,746
Let's go to bed.
Come on.

914
00:54:59,863 --> 00:55:02,566
Joe, Paulie's all upset

915
00:55:02,566 --> 00:55:06,069
about that piece Al Post did
on his radio show last night.

916
00:55:06,069 --> 00:55:09,840
Said you benched him
for not hustling after
that ball in the 7th.

917
00:55:09,840 --> 00:55:11,642
Post is a son of a bitch.

918
00:55:11,642 --> 00:55:14,645
Yeah, but you're gonna
have to talk to Paul.

919
00:55:14,645 --> 00:55:18,582
I'll talk to Paulie,
and I'll do more than that.

920
00:55:18,582 --> 00:55:20,984
[laughing]

921
00:55:20,984 --> 00:55:24,054
Al, where'd you get
the information for that piece
you ran last night?

922
00:55:24,054 --> 00:55:26,623
Well, I, uh, covered
a lot of stuff last night.

923
00:55:26,623 --> 00:55:28,892
Relief-pitching home runs
are way down.
I talked about that.

924
00:55:28,892 --> 00:55:31,995
Don't get cute with me.
You know what I'm talking about.
No. Tell me.

925
00:55:31,995 --> 00:55:34,631
I benched Paulie O'Neill.
That's what you said.
Yeah, I know.

926
00:55:34,631 --> 00:55:37,801
I was watching the game, Joe.
You took him out, I didn't.
Don't mess with me!

927
00:55:37,801 --> 00:55:40,737
I don't appreciate you
trying to stir up something
in this clubhouse.

928
00:55:40,737 --> 00:55:43,907
Well, he could've caught
the ball on the fly.
Instead, he one-hops it.

929
00:55:43,907 --> 00:55:45,909
Next inning,
you sent Rivera out to play.

930
00:55:45,909 --> 00:55:48,412
Now, tell me,
what part of that
did I get wrong?

931
00:55:48,412 --> 00:55:50,781
Except for sending Rivera out,
all of it.

932
00:55:50,781 --> 00:55:52,983
The next time you wanna talk
about why I did something,

933
00:55:52,983 --> 00:55:55,018
you come to me and you ask me,
and I'll tell you.

934
00:55:55,018 --> 00:55:57,688
Paulie O'Neill is playing
on legs that would
have you lying in bed,

935
00:55:57,688 --> 00:55:59,122
moaning for somebody
to bring you soup.

936
00:55:59,122 --> 00:56:01,158
He's out there every day
busting his ass!

937
00:56:01,158 --> 00:56:03,794
And if it weren't for him,
we wouldn't be in first place.

938
00:56:03,794 --> 00:56:05,796
You understand?
He's a team player.

939
00:56:05,796 --> 00:56:08,432
That's something
you would know nothing about!
I took him out

940
00:56:08,432 --> 00:56:11,034
'cause I could see his legs
were hurting, and I need him
the rest of the way!

941
00:56:11,034 --> 00:56:14,037
Those are the facts!
And if you were
doing your job,

942
00:56:14,037 --> 00:56:16,373
you'd have got it right
before you went on the air!

943
00:56:19,843 --> 00:56:21,678
That's it right there.

944
00:56:21,678 --> 00:56:23,113
Tell him, Coach.

945
00:56:23,113 --> 00:56:25,115
[chattering]

946
00:56:26,717 --> 00:56:28,785
So, what do you hear
from Steinbrenner?

947
00:56:28,785 --> 00:56:31,121
He's gotta be on your case
now that Baltimore's back in it.

948
00:56:31,121 --> 00:56:33,757
I hear nothing.
That's worse.

949
00:56:33,757 --> 00:56:35,192
Why is it worse?

950
00:56:35,192 --> 00:56:37,861
He already decided
to fire you.
I know it.

951
00:56:37,861 --> 00:56:39,863
[chuckles]

952
00:56:39,863 --> 00:56:43,066
Frankie, the last time
that Joe Torre was fired,

953
00:56:43,066 --> 00:56:44,801
he was finished.

954
00:56:44,801 --> 00:56:46,837
It was over, done.

955
00:56:46,837 --> 00:56:48,939
This thing is all
a big gift to me.

956
00:56:48,939 --> 00:56:52,075
They give you an extra life,
and you live it
as long as you can.

957
00:56:52,075 --> 00:56:54,811
And then when it's over,
it's over.

958
00:56:54,811 --> 00:56:56,813
What the hell
are you talking about,

959
00:56:56,813 --> 00:56:58,982
managing the Yankees
or a heart transplant?

960
00:56:58,982 --> 00:57:00,984
[chuckling]

961
00:57:03,520 --> 00:57:05,956
Joey.

962
00:57:05,956 --> 00:57:07,724
<i>[radio show caller]</i>
<i>The last thing this team needs</i>

963
00:57:07,724 --> 00:57:09,760
<i>is playing the Mariners</i>
<i>in Seattle.</i>

964
00:57:09,760 --> 00:57:12,162
<i>Ever since</i>
<i>the play-offs last year,</i>
<i>those guys hate each other.</i>

965
00:57:12,162 --> 00:57:13,930
<i>They just hate each other.</i>

966
00:57:13,930 --> 00:57:15,499
Come on, man.
That was last year.

967
00:57:15,499 --> 00:57:17,067
They're out
to get us every year.

968
00:57:17,067 --> 00:57:18,835
If they throw at
another one of our hitters--

969
00:57:18,835 --> 00:57:20,837
"Hitters"? Me.

970
00:57:20,837 --> 00:57:23,740
They throw at my head
every time I go up there.

971
00:57:23,740 --> 00:57:26,243
Man, what you
gonna do about that?

972
00:57:26,243 --> 00:57:28,745
<i>[TV announcer]</i>
<i>O'Neill gets knocked down. </i>
[crowd groaning]

973
00:57:28,745 --> 00:57:32,716
<i>It happened again.</i>
<i>Seattle has done this</i>
<i>repeatedly to Paul O'Neill.</i>

974
00:57:32,716 --> 00:57:34,918
<i>And he gets up.</i>
<i>He doesn't like it a bit.</i>

975
00:57:34,918 --> 00:57:37,921
<i>The umpire gets between O'Neill</i>
<i>and the Seattle catcher. </i>
[crowd shouting]

976
00:57:37,921 --> 00:57:40,190
<i>Now they go at it.</i>
<i>O'Neill knocks him down.</i>

977
00:57:40,190 --> 00:57:42,726
<i>And the benches</i>
<i>start to empty, Mike.</i>

978
00:57:42,726 --> 00:57:44,861
<i>We're gonna have a brawl.</i>
<i> [Mike]</i>
<i> We are gonna have a brawl.</i>

979
00:57:44,861 --> 00:57:48,198
<i> It's going to be nasty too.</i>
<i> These two teams</i>
<i> hate each other.</i>

980
00:57:48,198 --> 00:57:50,734
<i> They've hated each other</i>
<i> for a long time.</i>

981
00:57:50,734 --> 00:57:52,269
That's awful.

982
00:57:52,269 --> 00:57:55,939
Sometimes that's all
a team needs to get fired up.

983
00:57:55,939 --> 00:57:59,076
Something better
get them fired up.
They've lost four in a row.

984
00:57:59,076 --> 00:58:01,144
Hey, do you have to remind me?

985
00:58:01,144 --> 00:58:04,781
That's not good
for my heart condition.
Oh.

986
00:58:04,781 --> 00:58:06,783
[thud]
[chattering]

987
00:58:10,620 --> 00:58:13,857
What the hell is this, huh?
They throw at us,
and we do nothing to them!

988
00:58:13,857 --> 00:58:15,859
Relax, man.
Wasn't his fault.
Oh, no?

989
00:58:15,859 --> 00:58:17,828
Our pitchers
have to protect us.

990
00:58:17,828 --> 00:58:19,863
Come on, man.
There was nothing he could do.
He got warned.

991
00:58:19,863 --> 00:58:22,766
Warned? They throw
at Paul O'Neill twice,
and you don't do nothing!

992
00:58:22,766 --> 00:58:25,168
[overlapping shouting]

993
00:58:28,305 --> 00:58:30,974
The enemy is out there!

994
00:58:30,974 --> 00:58:33,043
On the ball field!

995
00:58:40,050 --> 00:58:42,352
[door opens, closes]

996
00:58:42,352 --> 00:58:44,588
[chattering]

997
00:58:52,596 --> 00:58:54,598
Oh, she walked?

998
00:58:54,598 --> 00:58:58,068
[laughs]
Yeah, well-- Oh, I see.

999
00:58:58,068 --> 00:59:01,004
Held onto the wall,
but it's still walking, right?

1000
00:59:01,004 --> 00:59:03,940
Yeah.

1001
00:59:03,940 --> 00:59:06,143
Ali, I love you so much.

1002
00:59:08,912 --> 00:59:12,082
These road trips
are just tough.
They're tough.

1003
00:59:12,082 --> 00:59:15,285
I miss you.
I miss you two.

1004
00:59:15,285 --> 00:59:17,888
All right.
Kiss her for me.

1005
00:59:17,888 --> 00:59:20,023
I love you.
Talk to you tomorrow.

1006
00:59:20,023 --> 00:59:21,291
Bye.

1007
00:59:26,062 --> 00:59:28,999
<i>The pitch.</i>
<i>Hit on the ground</i>
<i>toward short.</i>

1008
00:59:28,999 --> 00:59:32,068
<i>Jeter boots it.</i>
<i>Fields, fires low and wide.</i>

1009
00:59:32,068 --> 00:59:34,871
<i>Past Duncan</i>
<i>to shallow right field.</i>

1010
00:59:34,871 --> 00:59:37,174
<i>Two runs will score</i>
<i>for the A's.</i>

1011
00:59:37,174 --> 00:59:40,277
<i> And the Yankees are</i>
<i> playing terrible baseball.</i>

1012
00:59:54,858 --> 00:59:57,260
Okay. Let's go,
you bathing beauties.

1013
00:59:57,260 --> 01:00:00,197
Joe wants to talk to you.

1014
01:00:00,197 --> 01:00:02,332
[chattering]

1015
01:00:02,332 --> 01:00:05,268
What's going on?

1016
01:00:05,268 --> 01:00:07,671
All right.

1017
01:00:09,239 --> 01:00:12,008
Run your ass, boys.
It's not gonna be pretty.

1018
01:00:12,008 --> 01:00:13,610
[scoffs]

1019
01:00:18,014 --> 01:00:19,149
All right.

1020
01:00:21,218 --> 01:00:24,321
We have
a two-and-a-half game lead,

1021
01:00:24,321 --> 01:00:26,957
and we are gonna win this thing.

1022
01:00:26,957 --> 01:00:29,893
That's not a guess.
That's not a promise.

1023
01:00:29,893 --> 01:00:32,095
That is a fact.

1024
01:00:32,095 --> 01:00:34,965
We are gonna win this thing.

1025
01:00:34,965 --> 01:00:37,200
And I wanna tell you
how proud I am of each

1026
01:00:37,200 --> 01:00:40,003
and every damn one of you.

1027
01:00:43,039 --> 01:00:45,041
Go and get some dinner.

1028
01:00:45,041 --> 01:00:47,043
I don't wanna see
any one of you here sooner

1029
01:00:47,043 --> 01:00:49,412
sooner than an hour and a half
before tomorrow's game.

1030
01:00:49,412 --> 01:00:51,915
No batting practice.

1031
01:00:55,986 --> 01:00:57,954
Damn straight
we gonna win it.

1032
01:00:57,954 --> 01:01:00,457
New York Yankees!
Come on!
Yeah!

1033
01:01:00,457 --> 01:01:03,360
All the way to October!
[chattering]

1034
01:01:03,360 --> 01:01:06,496
Charlie Hayes?
That's the best you can do?

1035
01:01:06,496 --> 01:01:08,965
He's a solid third baseman.

1036
01:01:08,965 --> 01:01:12,235
He's got a little pop
in his bat.
He's got ten home runs.

1037
01:01:12,235 --> 01:01:16,072
Boggs is tired.
His legs is bothering him.
His back is bothering him.

1038
01:01:16,072 --> 01:01:18,942
He's not driving the ball.
We need help at third.

1039
01:01:18,942 --> 01:01:20,944
The Orioles just
signed Eddie Murray.

1040
01:01:20,944 --> 01:01:23,246
Eddie Murray
is a great ballplayer.
He's got 3,000 hits,

1041
01:01:23,246 --> 01:01:27,117
1,500 RBI's,
500 home runs.

1042
01:01:27,117 --> 01:01:31,254
And I'm just looking
for a good, solid ballplayer
who can play third base.

1043
01:01:32,355 --> 01:01:35,158
You're the general manager.

1044
01:01:35,158 --> 01:01:37,761
I don't need a statement, Bull,
just a confirmation or a denial.

1045
01:01:37,761 --> 01:01:39,763
If you wanna talk,
let's talk about the trade.

1046
01:01:39,763 --> 01:01:41,531
Charlie Hayes?
We got that.
That's yesterday's news.

1047
01:01:41,531 --> 01:01:43,967
Klapisch is citing
an anonymous source
in the<i> Bergen Record</i>

1048
01:01:43,967 --> 01:01:45,535
that says that George
has decided to replace you.

1049
01:01:45,535 --> 01:01:47,971
I am still here, aren't I?
Isn't my statement enough?

1050
01:01:47,971 --> 01:01:50,040
So you're denying it.
You say you're not
gonna be fired.

1051
01:01:50,040 --> 01:01:52,242
I don't think about that.
The club's still in first place.

1052
01:01:52,242 --> 01:01:54,978
The lead's down
to two and a half.
It is still a lead, isn't it?

1053
01:01:54,978 --> 01:01:56,546
That is still first place.

1054
01:01:56,546 --> 01:01:58,548
What happens if you fall
out of first place?

1055
01:01:58,548 --> 01:02:02,252
If we blow a 12-game lead,
then we deserve to be fired,
Joe Torre and I.

1056
01:02:02,252 --> 01:02:05,221
You don't blame the passengers
when the plane crashes.
We fly the plane.

1057
01:02:05,221 --> 01:02:07,724
[overlapping questions]

1058
01:02:09,392 --> 01:02:11,094
It's over there.

1059
01:02:11,094 --> 01:02:13,196
[car horn honking]
[Ali]
Hey!

1060
01:02:13,196 --> 01:02:16,533
Hey, guys, I'll catch up
with you later, okay?

1061
01:02:16,533 --> 01:02:18,535
Hi.
Hi.

1062
01:02:18,535 --> 01:02:21,137
How are you?

1063
01:02:21,137 --> 01:02:23,006
What are you doing here?

1064
01:02:23,006 --> 01:02:25,008
Well, I had to
get out of the house.

1065
01:02:25,008 --> 01:02:27,210
The phone is ringing
off the hook.

1066
01:02:27,210 --> 01:02:29,312
What phone?
What are you talking about?

1067
01:02:29,312 --> 01:02:32,115
You haven't
seen the papers?
No.

1068
01:02:48,598 --> 01:02:51,234
Not only is George firing us,

1069
01:02:51,234 --> 01:02:54,537
but we're gonna fire ourselves.

1070
01:02:54,537 --> 01:02:57,507
[laughing continues]

1071
01:03:02,145 --> 01:03:05,115
I'm not gonna talk about that.
Do you wanna talk baseball?
I'll talk baseball.

1072
01:03:05,115 --> 01:03:07,217
Just one thing, Joe.
Did you talk to Watson?

1073
01:03:07,217 --> 01:03:09,219
Did he clear
that statement with you?

1074
01:03:09,219 --> 01:03:11,321
That's two things,
and it's not baseball.

1075
01:03:11,321 --> 01:03:13,623
I gotta check on some people.
[overlapping chatter]

1076
01:03:13,623 --> 01:03:16,626
Hey, Joe.
Off the record, if you want.

1077
01:03:16,626 --> 01:03:19,429
How's your brother?

1078
01:03:19,429 --> 01:03:22,632
I've got an aunt
in the same hospital.
How's he doing?

1079
01:03:22,632 --> 01:03:25,268
He's okay.
He's in good spirits.

1080
01:03:25,268 --> 01:03:27,270
He's got a bad heart.

1081
01:03:27,270 --> 01:03:29,472
Clock is ticking.

1082
01:03:29,472 --> 01:03:31,074
[chattering]

1083
01:03:31,074 --> 01:03:32,108
[bat smacks ball]

1084
01:03:32,108 --> 01:03:34,110
[players exclaiming]

1085
01:03:38,081 --> 01:03:39,416
<i> ♪♪ [rock]</i>

1086
01:03:39,416 --> 01:03:41,418
Talk to you a minute,
Boggsy?

1087
01:03:44,621 --> 01:03:46,823
Take it easy, man.

1088
01:04:01,571 --> 01:04:03,940
Charlie Hayes is coming in
this afternoon.

1089
01:04:03,940 --> 01:04:05,575
He was playing
out on the coast.

1090
01:04:05,575 --> 01:04:08,378
I want you to know
that you're my third baseman.

1091
01:04:08,378 --> 01:04:09,646
Right.

1092
01:04:09,646 --> 01:04:12,115
It's not a platoon thing.

1093
01:04:12,115 --> 01:04:14,451
I'm gonna give him
a little playing time
because I know you're tired.

1094
01:04:14,451 --> 01:04:17,654
We got a month to go,
and then the play-offs.

1095
01:04:17,654 --> 01:04:20,190
You okay with this?

1096
01:04:20,190 --> 01:04:22,192
Oh, don't worry about me.

1097
01:04:22,192 --> 01:04:24,194
It's not like that, Boggsy.

1098
01:04:24,194 --> 01:04:26,196
We're just trying to give you
a little rest.

1099
01:04:26,196 --> 01:04:28,465
We're gonna need you
in the stretch.

1100
01:04:33,136 --> 01:04:35,672
[player]
Wait up!

1101
01:04:35,672 --> 01:04:39,309
Hey, Ray.
Would you help me carry
this bat out to the field?

1102
01:04:39,309 --> 01:04:42,378
I'm a little too tired
to take it myself.

1103
01:04:45,548 --> 01:04:47,550
[chattering]

1104
01:04:52,689 --> 01:04:54,290
[crowd clapping rhythmically]

1105
01:04:54,290 --> 01:04:56,960
[chanting]
Let's go, Yankees!
[clapping]

1106
01:04:56,960 --> 01:04:59,395
[mutters]
Let's go, Yankees!

1107
01:04:59,395 --> 01:05:01,164
[Man]
Hey, Joe!

1108
01:05:01,164 --> 01:05:04,734
[crowd]
We're praying for Frankie!

1109
01:05:04,734 --> 01:05:06,936
We all are, Joe.

1110
01:05:08,671 --> 01:05:10,740
Thanks.

1111
01:05:10,740 --> 01:05:14,611
I kept telling myself,
"This time I got the horses.

1112
01:05:14,611 --> 01:05:16,579
"This time I'm gonna do it.

1113
01:05:16,579 --> 01:05:18,648
"All right.
The lead is cut down,
but that's okay.

1114
01:05:18,648 --> 01:05:20,283
We're gonna hold on."

1115
01:05:20,283 --> 01:05:21,718
But it really wasn't
until this week

1116
01:05:21,718 --> 01:05:23,486
when I began...

1117
01:05:23,486 --> 01:05:25,488
[snoring]

1118
01:05:29,726 --> 01:05:33,196
It's so up and down.
Some days he seems
so much better.

1119
01:05:33,196 --> 01:05:35,565
I'm afraid there'll be fewer
and fewer of those days, Joe.

1120
01:05:35,565 --> 01:05:37,467
There's gotta be something
we can do.

1121
01:05:37,467 --> 01:05:40,503
We can't do anything
until we locate
a suitable heart.

1122
01:05:40,503 --> 01:05:43,306
What are we gonna do,
just watch him slip away?
That can't be right.

1123
01:05:43,306 --> 01:05:45,408
There's gotta be something
we can do.

1124
01:05:45,408 --> 01:05:48,444
We're looking for
a healthy heart in a person
who has just died.

1125
01:05:48,444 --> 01:05:50,346
That doesn't happen
every day.

1126
01:05:50,346 --> 01:05:52,015
Well, how long can he wait?

1127
01:05:52,015 --> 01:05:54,250
If we're lucky,
if he's lucky,

1128
01:05:54,250 --> 01:05:56,252
maybe a month.

1129
01:06:15,271 --> 01:06:16,673
Any pain?

1130
01:06:16,673 --> 01:06:19,442
None.

1131
01:06:21,778 --> 01:06:25,448
<i>David Cone checks in</i>
<i>to get the sign.</i>

1132
01:06:25,448 --> 01:06:28,651
<i>Now off the stretch, he deals.</i>
<i>Struck him out!</i>

1133
01:06:28,651 --> 01:06:30,520
<i>Looking great.</i>
<i> He has great movement</i>

1134
01:06:30,520 --> 01:06:32,655
<i> for a guy who's been out</i>
<i> three months.</i>

1135
01:06:32,655 --> 01:06:34,290
Eighty pitches?

1136
01:06:34,290 --> 01:06:35,825
Eighty, ninety.
Somewhere in there.

1137
01:06:35,825 --> 01:06:37,594
No more than that.
He knows?

1138
01:06:37,594 --> 01:06:39,362
He knows.

1139
01:06:40,563 --> 01:06:42,565
<i>Cone checking the sign.</i>

1140
01:06:42,565 --> 01:06:45,268
<i>He'll deal</i>
<i>to Terry Steinbach 2-2.</i>

1141
01:06:45,268 --> 01:06:47,270
<i>The pitch.</i>
<i>Struck him out swinging!</i>

1142
01:06:47,270 --> 01:06:49,572
<i> Is this an incredible story</i>
<i> or what?</i>

1143
01:06:49,572 --> 01:06:51,474
Can you believe this guy?

1144
01:06:51,474 --> 01:06:53,810
Hasn't pitched in three months,
and look at him.

1145
01:06:53,810 --> 01:06:57,080
Yeah, I believe him.
I've known him a long time.

1146
01:06:57,080 --> 01:07:00,083
<i>[Announcer]</i>
<i>Two outs in the 6th.</i>
<i>Cone deals Larado.</i>

1147
01:07:00,083 --> 01:07:03,486
<i>Cut and a miss</i>
<i>by Terry Steinbach.</i>
<i>He struck him out again.</i>

1148
01:07:03,486 --> 01:07:06,656
<i> [2nd announcer]</i>
<i> Mike, do you believe this?</i>
<i> How great Cone is pitching?</i>

1149
01:07:06,656 --> 01:07:09,325
<i>I'll tell you what:</i>
<i>this is bad fiction.</i>
<i>Three months ago,</i>

1150
01:07:09,325 --> 01:07:11,694
<i>you had to wonder if</i>
<i>the guy was going to live--</i>
<i>he had an aneurysm,</i>

1151
01:07:11,694 --> 01:07:13,463
<i>and now he's on the mound</i>
<i>for the first time,</i>

1152
01:07:13,463 --> 01:07:14,664
<i>and he's pitching</i>
<i>a no-hitter!</i>

1153
01:07:14,664 --> 01:07:15,865
<i>You really have to</i>
<i>wonder, though,</i>

1154
01:07:15,865 --> 01:07:18,668
<i>how long does</i>
<i>Joe Torre let him go?</i>

1155
01:07:30,680 --> 01:07:32,448
Sixty.

1156
01:07:45,128 --> 01:07:47,330
<i>[Announcer]</i>
<i>Two out, bottom of</i>
<i>the seventh inning,</i>

1157
01:07:47,330 --> 01:07:48,831
<i>Cone pitching</i>
<i>a brilliant game,</i>

1158
01:07:48,831 --> 01:07:51,768
<i>his first game back</i>
<i>from aneurysm surgery.</i>

1159
01:07:51,768 --> 01:07:54,671
<i>He stares in</i>
<i>for the sign, sets,</i>

1160
01:07:54,671 --> 01:07:56,372
<i>and deals to Berroa.</i>

1161
01:07:56,372 --> 01:07:58,374
<i>Swung on and hit deep</i>
<i>to center field.</i>

1162
01:07:58,374 --> 01:07:59,876
<i>Bernie Williams on the run.</i>

1163
01:07:59,876 --> 01:08:03,379
<i>Going back, on the track.</i>
<i>At the wall, he leaps,</i>

1164
01:08:03,379 --> 01:08:05,515
<i>and what a play</i>
<i>by Bernie Williams!</i>

1165
01:08:05,515 --> 01:08:07,717
<i>And he keeps</i>
<i>the no-hitter alive!</i>

1166
01:08:17,760 --> 01:08:19,562
Am I done?

1167
01:08:19,562 --> 01:08:22,365
You're at 85, Coney.
You're done for today.

1168
01:08:22,365 --> 01:08:24,467
You know it is possible
I could have a quick 8th.

1169
01:08:24,467 --> 01:08:27,837
Even if you do,
you won't pitch the 9th.

1170
01:08:27,837 --> 01:08:29,639
You know I never pitched
a no-hitter before.

1171
01:08:29,639 --> 01:08:31,507
You leave it up to me,
I'm going back out there.

1172
01:08:31,507 --> 01:08:33,543
It's your call.

1173
01:08:34,744 --> 01:08:37,680
Get Mariano warmed up
for the 8th.

1174
01:08:38,948 --> 01:08:42,385
Coney, great game.

1175
01:08:45,555 --> 01:08:47,890
Good one, Coney.

1176
01:08:47,890 --> 01:08:49,926
Good job, Coney.

1177
01:08:49,926 --> 01:08:52,962
Way to go, Coney.

1178
01:08:52,962 --> 01:08:54,597
Coney! Good job, man.

1179
01:08:56,666 --> 01:08:59,569
These guys are gonna
win it all. I know it.

1180
01:09:01,204 --> 01:09:02,939
<i>[Announcer]</i>
<i>A packed house</i>
<i>at Yankee Stadium,</i>

1181
01:09:02,939 --> 01:09:05,775
<i>and the Yankees need</i>
<i>one more win</i>

1182
01:09:05,775 --> 01:09:08,544
<i>to clinch the American League</i>
<i>East championship,</i>

1183
01:09:08,544 --> 01:09:11,647
<i>and Mike, it would be</i>
<i>the first time in 15 years</i>

1184
01:09:11,647 --> 01:09:13,416
<i>the Yankees would</i>
<i>have won a pennant.</i>

1185
01:09:13,416 --> 01:09:14,917
<i> [Mike]</i>
<i> And these fans</i>
<i> are starved for it.</i>

1186
01:09:14,917 --> 01:09:16,853
<i> The Yankees always</i>
<i> used to win, and now</i>

1187
01:09:16,853 --> 01:09:19,689
<i> there's been a long stretch,</i>
<i> a lot of dry land,</i>

1188
01:09:19,689 --> 01:09:22,492
<i> between the last time</i>
<i> and now.</i>

1189
01:09:22,492 --> 01:09:25,762
<i> The pitch to Fernando Viña</i>
<i> is popped up to center field!</i>

1190
01:09:25,762 --> 01:09:29,699
<i> Bernie Williams is there.</i>
<i> Bernie... makes the catch!</i>

1191
01:09:29,699 --> 01:09:32,969
<i> And the New York Yankees</i>
<i> have won the 1996</i>

1192
01:09:32,969 --> 01:09:34,704
<i> Eastern Division championship.</i>

1193
01:09:34,704 --> 01:09:36,973
<i> And the team is around</i>
<i> Jeff Nelson.</i>

1194
01:09:36,973 --> 01:09:40,209
<i> [announcers fade]</i>
[cries, laughs]

1195
01:09:51,788 --> 01:09:55,458
[wild cheering]

1196
01:10:01,464 --> 01:10:03,533
All right.

1197
01:10:05,768 --> 01:10:07,537
Yeah.

1198
01:10:11,808 --> 01:10:14,977
Ali, it's like someone's
playing a joke on me.

1199
01:10:14,977 --> 01:10:17,680
I used to think,
if I wanted it hard enough--

1200
01:10:17,680 --> 01:10:20,483
but that never worked.

1201
01:10:20,483 --> 01:10:24,554
So I say,
"Give me another chance.
Just one more chance."

1202
01:10:24,554 --> 01:10:28,758
And now that
it's almost there,

1203
01:10:28,758 --> 01:10:31,294
it's like they're saying,

1204
01:10:31,294 --> 01:10:33,963
"How much do
you want it, Joe?

1205
01:10:33,963 --> 01:10:35,498
Take your brother away?"

1206
01:10:35,498 --> 01:10:38,034
Oh, Joe, it's not like that.

1207
01:10:38,034 --> 01:10:40,570
You know that!

1208
01:10:44,040 --> 01:10:46,676
[cheers, whistles]

1209
01:10:46,676 --> 01:10:49,278
♪♪ [country]

1210
01:11:04,093 --> 01:11:06,763
[chuckles]
Hey, come on, guys.
We're not here to talk about me.

1211
01:11:06,763 --> 01:11:08,865
I'm just a guy
with a bum ticker.

1212
01:11:08,865 --> 01:11:11,968
If you want me to talk, you
want to talk about my brother.

1213
01:11:11,968 --> 01:11:15,772
I mean, we just won
the first round of the playoffs!

1214
01:11:15,772 --> 01:11:18,841
How 'bout that?
That was great baseball.

1215
01:11:18,841 --> 01:11:20,343
Tremendous baseball!

1216
01:11:22,111 --> 01:11:25,081
[cheering]

1217
01:11:25,081 --> 01:11:27,049
<i>[radio announcer]</i>
<i>Sal from the Bronx,</i>
<i>you're on the air!</i>

1218
01:11:27,049 --> 01:11:28,918
<i>What's on your mind?</i>

1219
01:11:28,918 --> 01:11:30,920
<i> [Sal]</i>
<i> Fielder, Jeter, Bernie,</i>
<i> O'Neill--</i>

1220
01:11:30,920 --> 01:11:33,656
<i> No way the Orioles</i>
<i> can beat these guys!</i>

1221
01:11:43,566 --> 01:11:46,803
[loud cheers]

1222
01:12:02,585 --> 01:12:04,720
Do you know
what I believe?

1223
01:12:04,720 --> 01:12:08,691
Do you want to know what
I believe in my heart?

1224
01:12:08,691 --> 01:12:11,027
When that boy
touched that ball,

1225
01:12:11,027 --> 01:12:14,697
that was my brother Rocco
reaching down to help Joey.

1226
01:12:14,697 --> 01:12:17,867
[Rae]
So, what can I tell ya?

1227
01:12:17,867 --> 01:12:20,970
Joey made 'em
into a real team.

1228
01:12:20,970 --> 01:12:24,974
Not just a bunch of
strangers playin' a game,

1229
01:12:24,974 --> 01:12:27,009
but-but people.

1230
01:12:27,009 --> 01:12:28,911
[cheering]

1231
01:12:31,781 --> 01:12:34,116
<i>[Announcer]</i>
<i>Yankees lead 9-3, 2 out,</i>
<i>bottom of the 9th,</i>

1232
01:12:34,116 --> 01:12:35,818
<i>and Cal Ripken up.</i>

1233
01:12:35,818 --> 01:12:37,887
<i>For the Yankees, it all</i>
<i>comes down to one out.</i>

1234
01:12:37,887 --> 01:12:39,856
<i>If they win, they go</i>
<i>to the World Series</i>

1235
01:12:39,856 --> 01:12:41,791
<i>for the first time</i>
<i>in 19 years.</i>

1236
01:12:41,791 --> 01:12:43,993
<i>For Joe Torre, he'll go</i>
<i>to the World Series</i>

1237
01:12:43,993 --> 01:12:46,896
<i>for the first time</i>
<i>in his long, 36-year career</i>

1238
01:12:46,896 --> 01:12:48,164
<i>as player and manager.</i>

1239
01:12:48,164 --> 01:12:50,166
<i>What a moment for Joe:</i>
<i>his brother Frank,</i>

1240
01:12:50,166 --> 01:12:53,035
<i>the memory of</i>
<i>his brother Rocco.</i>

1241
01:12:53,035 --> 01:12:55,204
<i>One out to go,</i>
<i>Wetteland deals--</i>

1242
01:12:55,204 --> 01:12:57,173
<i>Ripken hits</i>
<i>a ground ball to short.</i>

1243
01:12:57,173 --> 01:13:00,710
<i>Jeter fields, throws--</i>
<i>low and dug out by Martinez!</i>

1244
01:13:00,710 --> 01:13:04,780
<i>In time!</i>
<i>And the Yankees win!</i>
<i>The Yankees win!</i>

1245
01:13:04,780 --> 01:13:08,884
<i>The New York Yankees</i>
<i>have won the American</i>
<i>League championship,</i>

1246
01:13:08,884 --> 01:13:11,954
<i>and they're on their way</i>
<i>to the World Series.</i>

1247
01:13:38,948 --> 01:13:41,250
Doctor. How are you doing?
Congratulations.

1248
01:13:41,250 --> 01:13:44,053
You got to find him a heart!

1249
01:13:44,053 --> 01:13:46,956
Yeah, Joey's been MVP,
but, uh,

1250
01:13:46,956 --> 01:13:48,991
he's never been on
a world champion team,

1251
01:13:48,991 --> 01:13:51,227
either as a player
or as a manager,

1252
01:13:51,227 --> 01:13:53,229
so he's waited
a hell of a long time.

1253
01:13:53,229 --> 01:13:55,698
Makes it all the sweeter,
believe me. [chuckles]

1254
01:13:58,067 --> 01:14:01,504
<i>[New Yorker #1] The Yanks!</i>
<i>The second-best thing in my</i>
<i>life, next to marrying my wife.</i>

1255
01:14:01,504 --> 01:14:03,973
<i> [New Yorker #2]</i>
<i> It's the best!</i>
<i> It's a dream come true!</i>

1256
01:14:03,973 --> 01:14:07,543
<i> It's fantastic!</i>
<i> The Yanks are back!</i>
<i> They're back!</i>

1257
01:14:07,543 --> 01:14:09,946
<i>Sweep! Four games!</i>
<i>All over! Gone!</i>

1258
01:14:09,946 --> 01:14:12,148
<i>[TV announcer]</i>
<i>Here we are in game one</i>
<i>of the World Series,</i>

1259
01:14:12,148 --> 01:14:15,117
<i>and the Yankees</i>
<i>are getting clobbered.</i>

1260
01:14:15,117 --> 01:14:17,219
<i>The Bomber bats</i>
<i>are asleep tonight,</i>

1261
01:14:17,219 --> 01:14:19,889
<i>and Atlanta is on fire!</i>

1262
01:14:22,124 --> 01:14:25,728
[Yankee crowd booing]

1263
01:14:31,300 --> 01:14:34,236
[ball hits pole]

1264
01:14:34,236 --> 01:14:35,905
[Steinbrenner]
We're up against
Maddux tomorrow.

1265
01:14:35,905 --> 01:14:39,075
Do these guys
know what this is?

1266
01:14:39,075 --> 01:14:41,143
Thirty million people, and
we get our butts kicked, 12-0.

1267
01:14:41,143 --> 01:14:43,245
Ten.
That's not just losing.

1268
01:14:43,245 --> 01:14:45,114
People lose.
This is being humiliated.

1269
01:14:45,114 --> 01:14:47,283
Hello, George.

1270
01:14:47,283 --> 01:14:51,153
[sighs] They tell me
that's the worst clubbing
in World Series history.

1271
01:14:51,153 --> 01:14:53,556
Yeah, it was pretty ugly.

1272
01:14:53,556 --> 01:14:54,991
[deep sigh]

1273
01:14:54,991 --> 01:14:57,293
Tomorrow's a must game, Joe.

1274
01:14:57,293 --> 01:14:59,829
Tomorrow we will probably lose.

1275
01:14:59,829 --> 01:15:01,964
But then, we'll go to Atlanta
and sweep three,

1276
01:15:01,964 --> 01:15:03,766
and clinch it
here on Saturday.

1277
01:15:04,900 --> 01:15:08,270
Judas Priest.

1278
01:15:08,270 --> 01:15:10,072
<i>[TV announcer]</i>
<i>Well, the Yankees</i>
<i>come down to Atlanta</i>

1279
01:15:10,072 --> 01:15:12,975
<i>trailing the World Champion</i>
<i>Braves two games to none,</i>

1280
01:15:12,975 --> 01:15:17,013
<i>about to face the best</i>
<i>pitching staff in baseball</i>
<i>in their own back yard.</i>

1281
01:15:17,013 --> 01:15:21,183
<i>[Stadium announcer]</i>
<i>...the American League Champion</i>
<i>New York Yankees...</i>

1282
01:15:21,183 --> 01:15:24,854
<i>number six, Joe Torre!</i>

1283
01:15:24,854 --> 01:15:27,289
<i> [cheering]</i>

1284
01:15:39,368 --> 01:15:42,605
<i>[TV announcer]</i>
<i>Swung on by Leyritz, and</i>
<i>driven to deep left field.</i>

1285
01:15:42,605 --> 01:15:45,207
<i>Jones back to the track,</i>
<i>he's at the wall,</i>

1286
01:15:45,207 --> 01:15:47,276
<i>he leaps, and it's gone!</i>

1287
01:15:47,276 --> 01:15:50,246
<i>Bernie heading home,</i>
<i>he slides, he scores!</i>

1288
01:15:53,315 --> 01:15:56,152
<i>Right center field, Grissom...</i>
<i>drops the ball!</i>

1289
01:15:56,152 --> 01:15:57,920
<i>He dropped the ball!</i>

1290
01:15:59,855 --> 01:16:01,157
<i>Drilled to deep right field.</i>

1291
01:16:01,157 --> 01:16:04,293
<i>It is high! It is far!</i>
<i>It is gone!</i>

1292
01:16:04,293 --> 01:16:06,295
<i>Another...</i>
<i>[fading]</i>

1293
01:16:10,332 --> 01:16:14,103
Like you said, Joe.
We're taking the series home.

1294
01:16:14,103 --> 01:16:17,139
[laughing]
You taste it, Joe?
I can taste it.

1295
01:16:17,139 --> 01:16:19,942
We play day after tomorrow,
we win day after tomorrow.

1296
01:16:19,942 --> 01:16:21,644
Dass it!

1297
01:16:21,644 --> 01:16:23,646
Hey, what are you?
A wizard or something?

1298
01:16:23,646 --> 01:16:27,349
That's exactly what you said!
Sorry, I didn't see you on--

1299
01:16:27,349 --> 01:16:31,320
No, I was just trying
to reach my brother.

1300
01:16:31,320 --> 01:16:35,858
There's no answer in his room.
Maybe his phone's just turned
off. Try the switchboard.

1301
01:16:37,393 --> 01:16:39,328
I'm afraid to.

1302
01:16:48,370 --> 01:16:50,873
<i> [Ali] Great win, Joe.</i>
<i> Congratulations!</i>

1303
01:16:50,873 --> 01:16:53,409
<i> You did it! I just knew...</i>
[beeps]

1304
01:16:53,409 --> 01:16:56,312
<i> [Frank]</i>
<i> You did it, Joey.</i>
<i> You did it.</i>

1305
01:16:56,312 --> 01:16:59,315
<i> Congratulations, kid.</i>

1306
01:16:59,315 --> 01:17:02,251
<i> Joey, I'm gonna do it too.</i>

1307
01:17:02,251 --> 01:17:05,721
<i> They found a heart.</i>

1308
01:17:12,261 --> 01:17:15,331
[sensors beeping]

1309
01:17:34,283 --> 01:17:37,152
[motor chugging]

1310
01:17:47,129 --> 01:17:51,700
Hey. Joey, Joey.

1311
01:17:53,102 --> 01:17:55,671
Joey!

1312
01:17:58,274 --> 01:18:01,210
I need...

1313
01:18:01,210 --> 01:18:03,245
six tickets
for tonight's game.

1314
01:18:07,483 --> 01:18:10,986
Um, I would, but I didn't
think you were gonna make it,

1315
01:18:10,986 --> 01:18:12,755
so I sold 'em.

1316
01:18:12,755 --> 01:18:15,758
[laughs, winces]

1317
01:18:15,758 --> 01:18:17,993
[laughing]

1318
01:18:17,993 --> 01:18:20,095
<i>[TV announcer]</i>
<i>There is no greater setting</i>

1319
01:18:20,095 --> 01:18:22,364
<i>for a World Series</i>
<i>than Yankee Stadium.</i>

1320
01:18:22,364 --> 01:18:25,200
<i>The Yankees have won</i>
<i>22 World Championships</i>

1321
01:18:25,200 --> 01:18:27,336
<i>and they are poised</i>
<i>for number 23</i>

1322
01:18:27,336 --> 01:18:30,406
<i>in front of a jam-packed</i>
<i>Yankee Stadium crowd.</i>

1323
01:18:30,406 --> 01:18:33,375
<i>This is really</i>
<i>the Home Office for baseball.</i>
[crowd going wild]

1324
01:18:33,375 --> 01:18:37,012
<i>It's all set up right here,</i>
<i>the Yankees are one out away.</i>

1325
01:18:37,012 --> 01:18:39,481
<i>[2nd TV announcer]</i>
<i>One out away, but Wetteland</i>
<i>has a tough out,</i>

1326
01:18:39,481 --> 01:18:42,218
<i>with the tying and</i>
<i>go-ahead runs on base.</i>

1327
01:18:42,218 --> 01:18:43,986
<i>Facing Mark Lemke.</i>

1328
01:18:43,986 --> 01:18:46,121
<i>It'll be a 2-2 pitch</i>
<i>to Lemke,</i>

1329
01:18:46,121 --> 01:18:48,791
<i>as Wetteland deals--</i>
<i>popped him up!</i>

1330
01:18:48,791 --> 01:18:51,994
<i>Off-third foul!</i>
<i>Does Hayes have a play?</i>

1331
01:18:51,994 --> 01:18:54,997
<i>Hayes toward the dugout--</i>
<i>Hayes reaching in...</i>

1332
01:18:54,997 --> 01:18:57,132
<i>and he can't make the catch!</i>

1333
01:18:57,132 --> 01:18:59,301
<i>As Hayes falls down</i>
<i>in the Braves' dugout.</i>

1334
01:18:59,301 --> 01:19:02,304
[crowd groans]
<i>The Yankees were</i>
<i>three inches away</i>

1335
01:19:02,304 --> 01:19:04,340
<i>from winning</i>
<i>the World Series!</i>

1336
01:19:04,340 --> 01:19:07,543
<i>Now Lemke gets</i>
<i>another crack at it.</i>

1337
01:19:07,543 --> 01:19:10,245
<i> Well, that's</i>
<i> baseball etiquette.</i>

1338
01:19:10,245 --> 01:19:12,548
<i> Nobody was</i>
<i> helping Charlie Hayes</i>
<i> in that Braves' dugout,</i>

1339
01:19:12,548 --> 01:19:14,550
<i> and now they have to do it</i>
<i> all over again.</i>

1340
01:19:14,550 --> 01:19:16,218
That guy can give you
a heart attack.

1341
01:19:16,218 --> 01:19:18,153
Hector, would you
shut the hell up!

1342
01:19:18,153 --> 01:19:19,488
I'm sorry.

1343
01:19:19,488 --> 01:19:22,291
<i>[TV announcer]</i>
<i>What drama. They were so close,</i>

1344
01:19:22,291 --> 01:19:24,526
<i>a couple of inches away,</i>
<i>and they would have</i>

1345
01:19:24,526 --> 01:19:29,298
<i>won the World Series,</i>
<i>and now Wetteland has to</i>
<i>throw at least one more pitch.</i>

1346
01:19:36,238 --> 01:19:38,240
[player]
Come on, Johnny!

1347
01:19:38,240 --> 01:19:43,312
Ten years ago,
I was one out away from
winning the World Series, Dunc.

1348
01:19:43,312 --> 01:19:45,047
I can't take it,
I can't take it!

1349
01:19:49,585 --> 01:19:51,487
Give it to him!

1350
01:19:53,489 --> 01:19:55,491
Come on!

1351
01:19:55,491 --> 01:19:58,193
What do you think?
He's gonna get him out
with this next pitch.

1352
01:20:00,062 --> 01:20:02,331
<i>And Wetteland deals to Lemke--</i>
<i>swing, and he popped him up!</i>

1353
01:20:02,331 --> 01:20:04,299
Get it, son, get it!

1354
01:20:04,299 --> 01:20:07,569
<i>The ball's in foul territory.</i>
<i>Will this one stay in play?</i>

1355
01:20:07,569 --> 01:20:12,074
<i>Hayes, waiting.</i>
<i>Charlie Hayes waiting</i>
<i>for the ball to come down.</i>

1356
01:20:23,218 --> 01:20:25,387
[cheering]

1357
01:21:36,558 --> 01:21:38,560
Yeaahhhh!
